    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="502"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1817</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden (<persName type="from"
                            >Myers</persName>) to the Minister in China (<persName type="to"
                            >Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d502fn3">Copy transmitted to the Department by the Consul
                        General at Mukden in his despatch of December 8, 1933; received January 5,
                        1934.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 867</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-06">December 6,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to this office’s
                    despatches Nos. 801 and 805 of July 11 and 28, 1933,<note n="4" xml:id="d502fn4"
                        >Neither printed.</note> respectively, concerning developments in the
                    settlement of American claims arising as a result of the Japanese occupation,
                    and to enclose herewith a copy of a letter<note n="5" xml:id="d502fn5">Not
                        printed.</note> from Mr. H. C. Reed, American Claims Representative,
                    reporting the final settlement of all claims which had been investigated and
                    approved by the Commission for the Liquidation of Claims.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M. S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Myers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
